title: For Sale:  Heckler & Koch SP5K NIB
postcontent: The new SP5K was developed by Heckler & Koch as a semiautomatic, civilian sporting pistol (hence the “SP” prefix) that matches the look and feel of the famous MP5K submachine gun. The SP5K is designed and manufactured to meet the definition of a civilian pistol and marks the return of the roller delayed blowback system to an HK commercial product. This operating system is legendary in its accuracy and reliability. Originally developed on the Heckler & Koch G3 rifle, it has been used on several HK firearms. The SP5K retains many of the critical features of the MP5, including its precision machined components and attention-to-detail quality. The SP5K is manufactured completely in Heckler & Koch’s Oberndorf factory in southwest Germany. The SP5K is a safe, robust, ergonomic large frame handgun. For more comfortable shooting, the SP5K is equipped with an elastic “bungee” sling. The sling is easily installed by snapping it onto the sling swivel hardware located on the rear of the receiver. Using the sling makes firing the SP5K more stable and reduces fatigue. The overall length of the SP5K is approximately 14 inches — slightly longer than an MP5K — due to its unique handguard. The SP5K hand guard is designed with special ergonomic and safety features to protect the shooter’s hand and provide a comfortable and stable grip. Despite its size, the SP5K is well suited for sporting use. Using the proven roller delayed blowback system; the SP5K’s inherent accuracy makes it an excellent choice for target shooting and an ideal home security arm.

title: For Sale:  *** SOLD ***IWI US Jericho 941 9mm (Midsized)
postcontent:
The IWI US Jericho 941 is a timeless classic based off of the CZ-75 short recoil system. The 941 has evolved over the last 25 years under multiple names, the UZI Eagle, the Baby Eagle and the Baby Eagle II to name a few. Known for its innovative design that allows the slide to ride inside the rails, therefore providing a much preferred lower bore axis.  Another distinguishing design element was that IWI also wisely placed the slide lock/release and the manual safety controls for the 941 on the frame rather than the slide.
It can be carried either cocked & locked single action function, or hammer down double action function. It also includes an integral Picatinny rail, and adjustable dovetailed sights. This particular all steel model has been upgraded with Hogue rubber grips. The standard factory black synthetic grips are also included.
This all steel 9mm 941 comes with a total of two factory 16 round steel magazines and two holsters, one IWI factory Jericho polymer holster with adjustable cant and one felt lined nylon/kydex Front Line belt holster.
This like new 941 is flawless and comes with the factory IWI US shipping/range case, with all original materials, including owners manual, original factory grips, cleaning brushes and an extra 16 round factory magazine.
Prefer local sale and purchaser must be willing to provide a photo ID. If not picked up locally, purchaser responsible for all shipping and receiving FFL fees.
Very reasonably priced at $450.
